+# Enable with: CMAKE_ARGS='-DMICROPY_DISABLE_NETWORK=ON' AND the environment
+# variable MICROPY_DISABLE_NETWORK=1 (build_firmware.sh sets both).
+#
+# WHY the env var: ESP-IDF evaluates component CMakeLists an extra time in
+# SCRIPT MODE during early component expansion, and the REQUIRES collected in
+# that pass feed the component dependency graph. -D cache variables do NOT
+# exist in script mode, so with only the -D this file reports the networked
+# IDF_COMPONENTS list in the early pass — the network components then enter
+# the graph and compile (harmlessly unlinked, but present). The environment
+# variable IS visible in script mode, so both passes agree and the network
+# components never enter the build at all.
+option(MICROPY_DISABLE_NETWORK "Disable networking/Wi-Fi stack in ESP32 MicroPython build" OFF)
